---
// src/pages/family-documents.astro
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Family Documents" description="Future protected worksheets and family resources for Mr. Sayers' 3rd Grade Class.">
	<section class="panel section prose">
		<p class="eyebrow">Family Documents</p>
		<h2 class="page-title">Secure family documents will be ready later</h2>
		<p class="page-intro">
			Family Documents will eventually provide signed-in families with published worksheets and classroom resources. Secure family access
			is being prepared, but files are not exposed yet.
		</p>
		<div class="grid cards">
			<article class="card">
				<h4>Planned later</h4>
				<p>Published worksheets, permission slips, and family resources can be added when secure access is ready.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h4>Current state</h4>
				<p>For now, the page keeps the future area in the site structure so families know where it will appear later.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
